Privacy Policy for Hourme

Last Updated: 15.01.1995

At Hourme, your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our application.

1. General Information

App Name: Hourme

Purpose: Hourme is a calculator application that assists users with time-based calculations.

Data Collection: Hourme does not collect or store any personal information.

2. Data Collection and Use

No Personal Data Collected: Hourme does not collect, store, or process any personal data such as your name, email, or location.

Subscription Management: Hourme utilizes RevenueCat for managing subscriptions. While we do not collect your payment details, RevenueCat may process certain information in accordance with its own privacy policy.

3. Third-Party Services

RevenueCat: Hourme uses RevenueCat to manage subscriptions. RevenueCat may collect and process data necessary for subscription management, such as transaction details. Please review RevenueCat’s privacy policy for more information.

Hourme is not responsible for data collection or processing by third-party services.

4. Children’s Privacy

Hourme is available to users of all ages. However, we do not knowingly collect personal data from children.

If you believe a child has provided personal information through third-party services linked to Hourme, please contact the respective third-party service provider directly.

5. Security

Hourme does not store or process user data directly within the app, reducing risks to your data privacy.

We rely on Apple’s App Store infrastructure and RevenueCat’s secure systems for subscription management.

6. User Rights

Since Hourme does not collect personal data, there are no user rights related to accessing, modifying, or deleting data within the app.

For subscription-related inquiries, please refer to your Apple App Store account settings or RevenueCat’s privacy policy.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy as needed to reflect changes in the app or applicable laws.

Changes will be posted within the app and are effective immediately upon posting.

8. Contact Information

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at [Insert Contact Email].

Thank you for trusting Hourme!
